{
  "text": "Activated macrophages can also produce IL-10 which plays a key role in limiting immune-mediated pathology during many diseases. This anti-inflammatory cytokine ameliorates the excessive production of TNF-\u03b1 which can result in immunopathology during infections [CITATION_1] . In this study, treatment of ",
